quran[11]{c,v,t,f}:
  43,23,"Likewise, We never sent any warner to a town before you except that its affluent ones said, “We found our forefathers on a path, and we are following their footsteps.”",""
  43,24,"[The warner] said, “Even if I bring you a better guidance than what you have found your forefathers upon?” They said, “We totally reject what you [prophets] have been sent with.”",""
  43,25,"So We took revenge on them; see what was the end of the deniers!",""
  43,26,"And [remember] when Abraham said to his father and his people, “I disown all that you worship,",""
  43,27,"except the One Who created me; He will surely guide me.”",""
  43,28,"And he made it<sup>9</sup> a lasting word among his descendants, so that they may return [to Allah].","[9] i.e., his testimony of faith that none has the right to be worshiped except Allah."
  43,29,"However, I let these [Makkans] and their forefathers<sup>10</sup> enjoy their lives, until there came to them the truth and a clear messenger<sup>11</sup>.","[10] i.e., the descendants of Abraham (ﷺ).\n [11] i.e., Prophet Muhammad (ﷺ)."
  43,30,"But when the truth came to them, they said, “This is magic, and we definitely reject it.”",""
  43,31,"And they said, “Why was this Qur’an not sent down to a great man from one of the two towns<sup>12</sup>?”","[12] i.e., Makkah and its neighboring town; Tā’if."
  43,32,"Is it they who distribute the mercy of your Lord? It is We Who have distributed their livelihood among them in the life of this world, and have raised some of them above others in ranks, so that they may serve one another. But the mercy of your Lord is better than what they accumulate.",""
  43,33,"Were it not that all people might become a single community [of disbelievers]<sup>13</sup>, We would have given those who disbelieve in the Most Compassionate One houses of sliver roofs and staircases to ascend,","[13] Assuming that Allah’s generosity to them was a sign of His approval."
